<div><h3>ENG 125 - Medical Ethics in Science Fiction </h3>  <p><hr><span style="font-family:'palatino linotype', serif;">This First Year Intensive Seminar focuses on the ethical, legal, and social implications of medical science as interrogated through science fiction texts. Students will engage in a variety of writing assignments designed to think about not only literary genre (science fiction) but also larger social/ethical issues, exploring questions such as: <span style="color:rgb(70,70,69);">How does medical science as depicted in science fiction shape how we understand our humanity? Our personhood? And how does this culturally and historically contingent institution shape relationships, individual-to-individual, individual-to-group, and group-to-group?Â  </span></span></p>

<p><span style="font-family:'palatino linotype', serif;"><span style="color:rgb(70,70,69);">This course counts towards the Genre requirement in the English Major.</span></span><br><br><strong>Course Designation/Attribute:</strong> VP<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Periodically<br><br></p></div>		</td>
